  "signal_description": "The query retrieves data from the table 'defaultview-431'. It calculates various metrics related to the process cycle time for accounting cases. The 'Company Code' column is renamed as 'Company Code' in the result. The 'Number of Cases' column counts the number of 'case_id' values. The 'AVG Cycle Time' column calculates the average time difference between the last and first 'END_TIME' values. The 'Confirmation time for PRs' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Create PO Item' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Create PR Item'. The 'Processing time for POs' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Receive PO Item' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Create PO Item'. The 'PO Creation to Receive Invoice' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Receive Invoice' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Create PO Item'. The 'PO Creation to Submit PR Item' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Submit PR Item' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Create PO Item'. The 'Approval time for PRs' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Approve PR Item' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Create PR Item'. The 'Receive Invoice to Approve Invoice' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Approve Invoice' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Receive Invoice'. The 'Approve Invoice to Pay Invoice' column calculates the average time difference between the last 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Pay Invoice' and the first 'end_time' value with 'event_name' 'Approve Invoice'. The query filters out rows where 'Accounting Company Code' and 'PO Item Supplier ID' are not null, and the result is ordered by the second column in descending order."
}
